Five-year Accident History



Air Liquide's TI Boulevard location has never had an accident involving the covered process (propane) that caused deaths, injuries, property or environmental damage, evacuations, or sheltering in place.



Emergency Response Program



Air Liquide's TI Boulevard location utilizes an Emergency Action Plan, Emergency Response, Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), and operator training to ensure personnel are trained to identify and respond to accident and emergency situations.

Air Liquide's TI Boulevard location emergency response to accidental releases from the covered process includes: telephone notification of local fire department; telephone notification of DART; stopping and isolating equipment which may leak flammable gases; and isolation of the bulk propane tank via remote means.



